quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,25,"And give good tidings to those who believe and do righteous deeds that they will have gardens [in Paradise] beneath which rivers flow. Whenever they are provided with a provision of fruit therefrom, they will say, "
  2,26,"Indeed, Allāh is not timid to present an example - that of a mosquito or what is smaller{1} than it. And those who have believed know that it is the truth from their Lord. But as for those who disbelieve, they say, ",1:[Literally, "above it," i.e., greater in smallness.]
  2,27,"Who break the covenant of Allāh after contracting it and sever that which Allāh has ordered to be joined and cause corruption on earth. It is those who are the losers."